In northern Iraq , <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">U.S. Marines</COREF> and residents exchanged gunfire in <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">the city of Mosul</COREF> today , in the second day of civil disturbances there .
A senior Kurdish intelligence official says citizens were protesting the American occupation of <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">the city 's</COREF> main government building .
Seven Iraqis were killed by <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">U.S. Marines , who say they were responding to sniper fire</COREF> .
Hospital officials say 17 people have been killed and 18 wounded over the past 2 days .
Central Command says troops were involved in a gun battle yesterday .
